s by College Chairs’ Council: Facilitates and improves the work of faculty department chairpersons. Curriculum Committee: Agenda and minutes, meeting dates and responsibilities of this committee. Faculty Senate: The source for Faculty Senate information, including meeting agendas, files of past Senate meetings, and current listings of your Faculty Senators. Information Technology Governance Open Access Advisory Board (OAAB): The OAAB responsibilities will include providing guidance and oversight of the continued implementation of UNT policy 06.041, which covers access to and digital stewardship of scholarly works produced at UNT and to recommend changes to the policy to the Provost's Office and to the Faculty Senate for consideration. Space Planning and Management Committee (SPMC): The SPMC responsibilities will include broadening the scope, review, and discussion of space issues, moves, renovations, new construction, master planning and land acquisitions to ensure alignment with the Strategic Plan. This page contains pdf documents.  You can download a free pdf reader here. Visit Us   Office of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs370 Hurley Administration Building Mail Us   University of North TexasOffice of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs 1155 Union Circle #311190 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 [map]   Contact Us   940-565-2550 TTY: 940-369-8652 FAX: 940-565-2774 For questions about this website, contact ronda.bewley@unt.edu   Site last updated on: May 09, 2017 Disclaimer  |  AA/EOE/ADA  |  Privacy  |   Electronic Accessibility  |  State of Texas Online  |  Emergency Preparedness  |  THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information  |  UNT Compliance Hotline  |  Governors Committee on People with Disabilities  |  Texas Veterans Portal  |  UNT Home 